sql:
SELECT DISTINCT pa.user_id
FROM performance_analysis pa
WHERE ((pa.estimated_return - pa.actual_return) / pa.estimated_return * 100) > 10;

external_knowledge:
- "Highest ranked" refers to the users with the first name that comes first in alphabetical order; 
- "Verified KYC status" means the user has completed the Know Your Customer verification process;
- "More than one verified user" means there are at least two users from the same country with a verified KYC status.

-'financially active users' refers to users with at least one active stake (status = 'active') and total stake amount greater than 0; 
-'stepped into serious investment' refers to users with a verified KYC status (kyc_status = 'verified'); 
-'taken at least two major financial steps' refers to users who have made at least two transactions; 
-'clean financial record' refers to users with verified KYC status (kyc_status = 'verified').

sql:
SELECT total_bonded
FROM validators
WHERE validator_id = 0;

SELECT SUM(amount) AS total_unstaked_amount
FROM transactions
WHERE transaction_type = 'unstake';

external_knowledge:
- "Maximum stakes" refers to the highest stake amount associated with each user; 
- The ranking is determined based on the stake amounts in descending order;
- Users are considered to have the maximum stakes if they have the top-ranked stake amount.

sql:
SELECT stake_id, unstake_amount, remaining_blocks
FROM unstaking
WHERE status = 'pending';
